<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,1703,1874]" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis box="[189,253,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">Notes</emphasis>
:—The new species has grown on fruiting bodies of 
<taxonomicName box="[828,951,1703,1729]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Boletaceae</taxonomicName>
sp. containing only the asexual state. Among the known Boleticolous species of 
<taxonomicName box="[515,644,1740,1765]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[515,644,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">Hypomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jing Z. Sun" authorityYear="2021" box="[655,808,1739,1766]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ampullaris">
<emphasis box="[655,675,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[687,808,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">ampullaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Damon" authorityName="Damon" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Sepedonium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ampullosporum">
<emphasis box="[1134,1452,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">Sepedonium ampullosporum</emphasis>
Damon
</taxonomicName>
in forming candelabrum like conidiophores and producing ampulliform conidia. But 
<taxonomicName box="[1169,1373,1775,1802]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Sepedonium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ampullosporum">
<emphasis box="[1169,1183,1776,1802]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1197,1373,1775,1801]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">ampullosporum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having longer phialides (30–80 × 3.5 μm) and larger ampulloconidia (14–20 × 6–8 μm), and pigment discoloration of medium (
<bibRefCitation author="Damon, S. C." box="[273,423,1847,1874]" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" pagination="86 - 96" refId="ref6960" refString="Damon, S. C. (1952) Two noteworthy species of Sepedonium. Mycologia 44 (1): 86 - 96. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1952.12024172" type="journal article" year="1952">Damon 1952</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sahr, T. &amp; Ammer, H. &amp; Besl H. &amp; Fischer M." box="[434,614,1847,1873]" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" pagination="935 - 943" refId="ref8203" refString="Sahr, T., Ammer, H., Besl H. &amp; Fischer M. (1999) Infrageneric classification of the boleticolous genus Sepedonium: species delimitation and phylogenetic relationships. Mycologia 91 (6): 935 - 943. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1999.12061104" type="journal article" year="1999">
Sahr 
<emphasis box="[492,549,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
, 
